<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pill2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pill,</orth> vb. to pillage, to rob, to plunder: <cit><quote>the commons hath he --ed with grievous taxes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.246" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 246</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that which you have --ed from me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.159" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 159</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. by law,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 1, 12</bibl></cit>.
